caption.p: Effect of S. chamaecyparissus and T. patula essential oils on the concentration of hydrogen peroxide (mean ± SD) within tissues of M. persicae ( A) and R. padi ( B). Values marked by different letters are significantly different at p < 0.05 (Tukey’s test). Statistics for two-way ANOVA: ( A) treatment F 2,24 = 37.45, p < 0.001, time F 3,24 = 13.11, p < 0.001, treatment × time interaction F 6,24 = 7.17, p < 0.001; ( B) treatment F 2,24 = 59.49, p < 0.001, time F 3,24 = 14.76, p < 0.001, treatment × time interaction F 6,24 = 5.29, p < 0.01.
